Package edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.fitting

Interface Summary
ObjectiveFunction Describes a function that returns a (real) scalar and takes a vector of parameters.
 

Class Summary
DifferentialEvolutionMinimizer This class implements the differential evolution algorithm for function minimization.
GaussianFitter3D Performs a three-dimensional gaussian fit to an object in an image using a maximum likelihood method assuming Poisson distributed pixel intensities (once converted to units of photons).
GaussianImageObject An ImageObject that fits to a three-dimensional gaussian.
ImageObject An object in an image with some spatial extent that can be fit to some function.
NelderMeadMinimizer A function minimizer that implements the Nelder-Mead or Downhill Simplex method.
